transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra at Score Blue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I want to cancel any subscription. I never subscribed in more than one order, but I got another order and bill which I didn't request.

Speaker 1: Okay. Let me pull up your account and see what happened.

Speaker 2: First, could I get your full name and date of birth, please?

Speaker 1: Richard Bright.

Speaker 2: 2-2-5-7.

Speaker 1: Richard, I see your last order was...

Speaker 2: Refill was receiving the prescriptions written on December 21st for 100 milligram Viagra. Is that accurate?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I didn't... I never ordered that.

Speaker 2: The most recent one you're saying is in January. Yeah, it looks like the doctor had written this with refills.

Speaker 1: All right, so there's a total of 12 refills on the script once it's written.

Speaker 2: You're not...

Speaker 1: Authorized to authorize them to multiple...

Speaker 2: Subscriptions and I didn't request that.

Speaker 1: Sure. So it is, you know, this is fixable.

Speaker 2: So I said you're not required to; it's just that's how they write it with the lower milligram dosages and quantities.

Speaker 1: So in your case with 100, they just wrote it with refills. It is adjustable though, Richard.

Speaker 2: So, you know, this isn't a subscription. If you want, you can just pause it and then that would allow you to have access to...

Speaker 1: The remaining refills and call in and place orders as needed.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no, I'm good for now. I just want to make sure that I don't receive any more or get billed.

Speaker 1: Okay. So yeah, upon cancellation you would lose access to this medication.

Speaker 2: Any future prescriptions would require a new health consultation and survey, okay?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so just keep in mind. They're going to take a look here at your previous prescriptions.

Speaker 1: There might be a little bit of a delay just because of the cancellation, but if you're okay with that I can cancel.

Speaker 2: Yeah, cancel. I don't want to...

Speaker 1: Receive any more and I don't want to be billed for another order.

Speaker 2: Sure. Yep. I'll go ahead and cancel it for you. You're all set.

Speaker 1: Okay, great.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Yeah. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
